Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

While it comes to the boil, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop them into a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While it fries, peel and grate the @garlic clove{4} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @ground cinnamon{1%sachet}, @dried rosemary{1%sachet} and half the garlic to the beef. Fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto one side of a large #baking tray{}, cut-side up. Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the garlic bread.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @creme fraiche{150%g} with half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40%g}. Season with @pepper{}.

Once the beef sauce has thickened, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat. Stir in the cooked pasta, then spoon it into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Evenly spread the creme fraiche sauce over the pasta, then sprinkle on the remaining Parmigiano Reggiano cheese.

Put the dish onto the other side of the garlic bread baking tray and pop under the grill until it's bubbling and the garlic bread is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the tomatoes and mix together. Cut the garlic bread diagonally into triangles.

Serve your ultimate beef pasta with the garlic bread and salad alongside. Enjoy!